title: eGROCERY Web Application (Full stack)
description: Collaborated with four other software engineering students to develop a full stack e-commerce web application that enables users to browse a catalog of grocery items and purchase them with dedicated pages for help and support, user profile, order history and cart management.

title: Auctions Web Application
description: Developed a dynamic Django-powered web application for online auctions, featuring user registration, authentication, item posting, and bidding functionality. Utilized SQLite for streamlined storage and management of user and item data.

title: Personal Website
description: Developed a fully responsive full-stack portfolio website using React, Node.js, Express, and PostgreSQL. Designed an engaging user experience with dedicated pages for education, experience, and projects. Implemented a robust backend with visual CRUD, enabling efficient data management from the frontend.

title: Masters Admissions Predictor
description: Leveraged web scraping techniques to obtain a comprehensive dataset comprising credentials of Masters applicants from American Universities. By utilizing logistic regression in Python, we collectively trained a robust model that forecasts application outcomes based on given credentials.
